      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TUKI BEACH (1) was in winning form two back (16.45) at Q Straight but ran below best last time at this track, finishing 8th. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Rates on top in this line up. SHE'S TIP TOP (3) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Steele Wolf (20.16) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Expected to be in this for a long way. BUTTERNUT QUEEN (2) sailed across from an outside draw and gave a sight, holding on for second and beaten 0.8 lengths (20.15) at this track in a Grade 5 over 352m. Leading chance. SCRUB'S BLUE (4) has top-three aspirations after placing last time.",
